<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="54">Status. Until mid-20th century endemic to northern Black Sea liman coast, since then invasive elsewhere in Black Sea Basin, Volga catchment, western Europe, and North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="54">Type locality. Bug Liman near Nikolaev, Ukraine.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="54">
Distribution. Endemic to western Ukrainian liman coast, introduced in Danube Delta, Azov Sea, Volga catchment, western and central Europe, and North America (
<bibRefCitation author="Orlova, MI" journalOrPublisher="Aquatic Ecology" pageId="80" pageNumber="111" pagination="561 - 573" title="Range expansion of quagga mussels Dreissenarostriformisbugensis in the Volga River and Caspian Sea basin." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10452-005-0311-6" volume="38" year="2005">Orlova et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Coughlan, NE" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="73" pageNumber="104" url="https://doi.org/10.1051/kmae/2017037" year="2017">Coughlan et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="55">
<pageBreakToken pageId="24" pageNumber="55" start="start">Taxonomic</pageBreakToken>
notes. This species has been considered as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. rostriformis" pageId="24" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="rostriformis">D. rostriformis</taxonomicName>
(Deshayes, 1838) by some authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Orlova, MI" journalOrPublisher="Aquatic Ecology" pageId="80" pageNumber="111" pagination="561 - 573" title="Range expansion of quagga mussels Dreissenarostriformisbugensis in the Volga River and Caspian Sea basin." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10452-005-0311-6" volume="38" year="2005">Orlova et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
), yet we follow the argumentation of 
<bibRefCitation pageId="24" pageNumber="55">Kijashko in Bogutskaya et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
to consider it as a distinct species. The proposed synonymy of Caspian 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. rostriformis" pageId="24" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="rostriformis">D. rostriformis</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. grimmi" pageId="24" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="grimmi">D. grimmi</taxonomicName>
) and Black Sea 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. bugensis" pageId="24" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="bugensis">D. bugensis</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stepien, CA" editor="Nalepa, TF" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica" pageId="83" pageNumber="114" title="2 nd edition. CRC Press, Boca Raton" url="https://doi.org/10.1201/b15437-33" year="2013">Stepien et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
is discussed below under 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. grimmi" pageId="24" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="grimmi">D. grimmi</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
